OL,4,G2200FHow the Nazis Lost the War
OL,5,     GIn their pursuit of the Aryan
OL,6,     Gdream, the Nazis were burdened by
OL,7,     Ginternal ideological conflict,
OL,8,     Gwhich undermined their ability to
OL,9,     Gsucceed in WWII and ultimately
OL,10,     Gled to the deaths of millions.
OL,11,G2300FHow the Nazis Lost the War
OL,12,     GEarly victories in WWII gave
OL,13,     GHitler a dangerous over-
OL,14,     Gconfidence, which was later
OL,15,     Gtested and proven vulnerable. His
OL,16,     Ghubris and greed ultimately led
OL,17,     Gto Germany's defeat as time
OL,18,     Grevealed his flaws.
